{"word":"ὀδύρομαι","slug":"ὀδύρομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀδύρομαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>the <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b> use a form <el>δύρομαι</el> when required by the metre.\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>, mostly in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>impf.</a>,\n<p/><i>to lament, bewail, mourn for</i>:<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <el>ὁ δ' ὀδύρετο πατρίδα γαῖαν</el> <i>mourned for</i> it, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> for the want of it, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; so, <el>νόστον ὀδυρομένη</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to mourn for, for the sake of</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to wail</i> or <i>lament to</i> or <i>before</i> others, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to wail, mourn</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}